Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Would you believe it? Matt Henry gets Zak Crawley for the fifth time in this series, this time with a fantastic catch on his own bowling. He lands this on a hard length and on middle, angles in and then straightens a shy bit. Zak Crawley looks to work it away but closes the bat face early. It goes off the leading edge towards the bowler where Henry moves to his left, dives and grabs the ball just inches above the ground. Crawley is not sure about that and the umpires want to make sure as well. The replay shows that the fingers are underneath the ball and Crawley has to walk back after hitting a few lusty blows. England rocked early again!

Commentary: Did that come off the bat or glove? Bowled full and outside off, turning in. Tom Blundell premeditates the reverse sweep, misses it completely, goes off the toe and lobs up towards first slip. There is a slight appeal from the bowler but the umpire is unmoved. They challenge the decision as Harry Brook, the catcher thinks it is out. The replays show that it misses the inside edge of the bat and goes up in the air after ricocheting off the foot towards the slip. England wastes a review!

Commentary: OUT! LBW! That is one heck of a review! This one is bowled way fuller and on middle stump, turns away a shy bit, inviting a sweep. Joe Root obliges, leans on and looks to sweep, goes underneath the blade and thuds onto the front pad. Massive and a long appeal from men around the bat. The umpire isn't convinced. Tom Latham has a chat with the keeper and the bowler and opts for a review. UltraEdge comes up and from the side on view, it looks like the ball just sneaks underneath the bat and goes on to hit the pad. Ball Tracking shows that it hits in line and the impact is dead on the middle stump. New Zealand will be happy that they took this chance for a review and it is rewarded. Joe Root walks right after his half-century and New Zealand have their first breakthrough of the morning.
Default_Commentary: 25.5: Mitchell Santner to Joe Root, OUT! lbw b Mitchell Santner.
Howout: lbw b Mitchell Santner
